parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrochromic self-dimming mirror can cause the driver to be blinded or lose rear view capability, leading to accidents or reduced visibility.
symptoms: The mirror appears foggy or smoky
the mirror fails to dim against rear approaching headlights
the mirror has a delayed or no response to light
the mirror has water marks or cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning and Climate Control System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air conditioning and climate control system can cause the windows to fog up, reducing visibility and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Windows fog up when the air conditioning is turned off
the air conditioning system fails to provide fresh air
the vehicle's windows fog up regardless of temperature or humidity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windshield wiper and window system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or reduced safety.
symptoms: Windshield wipers bounce on the glass
windows leak or come off track
windshield wipers fail to clear the windshield properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light socket can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: the brake light bulbs burn out frequently
the brake light sockets melt or burn
the plastic around the socket melts
the socket is difficult to remove due to melting
the "bulb out" warning light is too dim or hidden from view.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manufacturer's Failure to Acknowledge and Address Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's failure to acknowledge and address the recall can lead to delayed or inadequate repairs, potentially causing harm to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: The manufacturer denies the existence of a recall
the manufacturer fails to provide necessary parts for repairs
the manufacturer fails to notify owners of recalls in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various symptoms, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of essential systems like brake lights, headlights, and dashboard lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: clicking sounds when trying to start the engine
and fogging of the rearview mirror.

The failure of the brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
